from a longer account of the careers of John and Carl Hagenbeck:
&quot;During the First World War, after what Lorenz calls John Hagenbeck’s &quot;adventurous escape from British internment [in Ceylon]&quot; via Java and Italy, John helped his nephew run the Stellingen (Hamburg) Animal Park in very difficult wartime circumstances. One conscripted Stellingen employee actually took his Ceylon Asian elephant &quot;Jenny&quot; along with him to the Western Front to drag timber for trench props, and entertain the delighted German troops with circus tricks in the evenings; Jenny became the only elephant to be listed in the Wehrmacht books as a &quot;war elephant&quot;! &quot;
